sentences: Louise Geneviève de La Hye née Rousseau (8 March 1810 - 17 November 1838) was a French pianist, organist and composer, who sometimes used the pseudonym M. Leon Saint-Amons.
She studied piano with her father and with Louis Joseph Saint-Amans, and in 1821 entered the Paris Conservatory.
Rousseau began teaching at the Conservatory in 1930, but moved to Cambrai after she married.
She had two children and returned to Paris in 1834 where she continued teaching and composing.
